quran[10]{c,v,t}:
  43,16,"Or even has He taken to Him, from what He creates, daughters and has elected for you (only) sons"
  43,17,"And when one of them is given the good tidings of what he struck (i.e., cited) as a likeness to The All-Merciful, (i.e., he is given the news of the birth of a daughter) his face lingers blackened, and he is constantly repressing anguish inwardly"
  43,18,Is he who is brought up amid ornaments and in adversariness is without (demonstrable) evidence (to be associated with Allah)
  43,19,"And they have made the Angels, who are the bondmen of The All-Merciful, females. Did they witness their creation? Their testimony will be written down, and they will be questioned (about it)"
  43,20,"And they have said, \"If The All-Merciful had (so) decided, in no way would we have worshiped them.\" In no way do they have any knowledge of that; decidedly they are (doing nothing) except conjecturing"
  43,21,"Or even have We brought them a Book even before it, (The Qur'an) so that they are upholding it fast"
  43,22,"No indeed, (but) they have said, \"Surely we found our fathers upon a course, (Literally: a nation: a community; following a leadership or a religion) and surely we are guided upon their tracks"
  43,23,"And thus in no way did We send even before you any warner into a town, except that its (population) living in ease and luxury said, \"Surely we found our fathers upon a course (Literally: a nation; a community; following a leadership pr a religion) and surely we are emulating (them) upon their tracks"
  43,24,"He said, \" (Even) if I should come to you with a better guidance than you found your fathers upon?\" They said, \"Surely we are disbelievers in what you have been sent with"
  43,25,Then We took vengeance upon them; so look into how was the end of the beliers